{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d1fefe41-9f71-40a7-a2b8-89e2212db385","content":"The template is **structurally valid** but **not ready to publish** as-is. Here's my assessment:\n\n### ✅ Required fields present\n`identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `tags.language`, `tags.type` — all good.\n\n### ⚠️ Issues to fix before publishing\n\n1. **Placeholder values** — `\"MyCompany\"`, `\"My Company\"`, `\"My Web API Template\"` look like placeholders. Replace with real branding.\n2. **Missing `$schema`** — Add `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"` for validation/IntelliSense.\n3. **Missing `description`** — NuGet gallery displays this; without it the listing looks incomplete.\n4. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Important for versioning and updating templates on NuGet (e.g., `\"MyCompany.WebApi\"`).\n\n### 💡 Minor suggestions\n- Consider adding `preferNameDirectory: true` for project templates.\n- Verify `net9.0` default is intentional (vs `net8.0` LTS).\n\nWould you like me to update the file with these fixes?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"708f4219-77cb-44f5-875c-bd56b7fabf1d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check against the .NET template engine schema requirements.\n\nIssues I see:\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Not required, but recommended for validation/IntelliSense.\n2. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Recommended for NuGet package templates so multiple versions/variants can be grouped.\n3. **Missing `precedence`** — Often paired with groupIdentity.\n4. **Missing `preferNameDirectory`** — Minor, but useful for project templates.\n5. **`defaultValue` of `net9.0`** — This is fine, but the user should verify it matches a valid TFM.\n\n\n6. **No `description`** — This is helpful but not strictly required in template.json.\n7. **No `thirdPartyNotices` or `postActions`** — Not required.\n\nThe core required fields are all present: `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author`, `tags.language`, `tags.type`, `classifications`, and `sourceName` for name replacement. So the template is actually ready for NuGet publishing—the missing fields are just nice-to-haves for better organization and discoverability. required* fields are `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, and `author`. The rest are recommended.\n\nFor NuGet publishing specifically, the `.nuspec` or `.csproj` packaging is what really matters. But looking at just template.json:\n\n**Not blocking but notable issues:**\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Recommended: `\"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"`\n2. **Missing `description`** — NuGet gallery shows this; without it the template listing looks incomplete.\n3. **Missing `groupIdentity`** — Important when you publish multiple related templates or update the template later.\n4. **Placeholder values** — `\"MyCompany\"`, `\"My Company\"`, `\"My Web API Template\"` look like placeholders that should be replaced with real values before publishing.\n\nThe template is structurally valid but needs those recommended fields filled in and the placeholder values replaced with actual metadata before publishing.","outputTokens":813,"requestId":"4048:1E8A:C6E3910:DD30462:69EC0F90"},"id":"3182d868-d740-45a7-aefa-e5b41c7f1a88","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:49:40.680Z","parentId":"c4f96af1-1c08-4070-8c87-3930244a03d5"}
